Thank you so much for the VC7 build. It's great to code in Visual Studio and
C++. This lastest build has renewed by interest in CANTERA (was limited to
python before).

I am trying to develope a combustor simulation with multiple reactors and am
having trouble lighting them all at once with a H igniters and the resulting
pressure pulse. Any suggestions for starting multilple combustion reactors at
once. I am also having trouble with the correct C++ syntax for
PressureRegulators. If a reactor has multple inputs, do I need a pressure
regulator on the output for each one?. Tryied flexible walls but the program
exited.

My model has premix,recirulation,primary, secondary, and dilution zone
reacters. When changing mass flow controller rates during the sim, does the
ReactorNet need resetting each time.

Just Starting but this is really fun !!!!
